Generated Narrative: ImplementationGuide inca.fhir.uv.osiris

OsirisImplementationGuide

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

https://ig-osiris.cancer.fr/ig/osiris/ImplementationGuide/inca.fhir.uv.osiris

An implementation guide about FHIR-osiris to store interoperable data about oncology, including genomics.

Analysis

resource.name: Annotation Reference
resource.description: The annotation reference profile indicates the reference genome / pfam domain / database used to generate the Annotation instance linked.

resource.name: Biological Sample
resource.description: Description of a biological sample coming from an oncology Patient, with its storage condition.

resource.name: Biomarker
resource.description: Biomarker Observation about a patient from BiomarkerCode ValueSet.

resource.name: Cancer Organization
resource.description: Cancer organization to describe the provider center or origin center of the onco-patient.

resource.name: Cause Of Death
resource.description: Observation that indicates the cause of death of an Oncology Patient.

resource.name: Clinical Trial Subject
resource.description: Subject that belongs to a oncology-related Clinical Trial.

resource.name: Connection with the imaging module
resource.description: Connection with the imaging module (ImagingStudy and ROI Segmentation)

resource.name: Consent for Genetic Data Usage
resource.description: The genetic consent resource indicates if a patient has given his authorization to share and use its genetics data.

resource.name: Family Cancer History
resource.description: History of cancer in an Onco Patient Family.

resource.name: Fusion Spanning Pairs
resource.description: Number of reads pairs spanning the fusion

resource.name: Fusion Split Reads
resource.description: Number of reads containing the fusion point

resource.name: Gene Expression
resource.description: Observation of a Gene Expression variant derived from a SequencingAnalysis. The Expression profile is used to indicate the actionability, the pathogenecity and the gene expression quantity of the gene of interest.

resource.name: Gene Expression Data Type
resource.description: Type of the expression value corresponding to the level of data processing

resource.name: Gene Expression Data Type Value Set
Gene Fusion
resource.description: Observation of a Gene Fusion derived from a SequencingAnalysis. The Fusion profile indicates the pathogenicity, the actionability and if the fusion has occured in the reading frame.

resource.name: Genome Entity
resource.description: The genome entity profile is used to indicate the genome reference used to build the Annotation.

resource.name: Imaging Device
resource.description: Qualification of the equipment used to acquire a series of images

resource.name: Imaging Study Injection
resource.description: Description of an imaging study injection.

resource.name: Location to the PACS server
resource.description: System communication to the PACS server

resource.name: Oncologic Adverse Event
resource.description: Adverse event related to a cancer-related treatment associated to a grade from MEDDRA terminology (ex: 10047700: "Vomiting").

resource.name: Oncology Clinical Trial
resource.description: Oncology clinical trial used to associate a Onco Patient to a Clinical Trial

resource.name: Oncology Surgery
resource.description: Oncology-related surgery with a description of the outcome using RECIST categorys.

resource.name: Oncology-related Medication Statement
resource.description: Medication statement related to a cancer cure.

resource.name: Patient Origin Center
resource.description: The origin center organization of an Oncology Patient.

resource.name: Performance Status
resource.description: Oncology-patient performance status observation (see https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK97482/ for more information).

resource.name: Radiomics Criteria
resource.description: Description of the criteria used for the biomarkers calculations

resource.name: Radiomics Features
resource.description: Description of the radiomics measurements described in IBSI nomenclature

resource.name: Radiomics Image Filters
resource.description: Filtering parameters used for the imaging analysis

resource.name: Radiotherapy course Summary
resource.description: A summary of a course of radiotherapy planned or delivered to a patient

resource.name: Radiotherapy Phase
resource.description: Summary of the radiotherapy phases planned or delivered to a patient

resource.name: Radiotherapy Plan
resource.description: Radiotherapy plans planned or delivered to a patient

resource.name: Radiotherapy Treatment Location Qualifier Value Set
resource.description: Various modifiers that can be applied to body locations where radiotherapy treatments can be directed.

resource.name: Radiotherapy Volume Profile
resource.description: A volume of the body treated by radiotherapy (plannes or delivered).

resource.name: Radiotherapy Volume Type Value Set
resource.description: Codes describing the types of body volumes used in radiotherapy planning and treatment. The value set includes the most common codes from DICOM CID 9534 Radiotherapy Targets (UID 1.2.840.10008.6.1.1244) and adds a code for Organs at Risk (OAR).

resource.name: Response Evaluation
resource.description: Response evaluation to an oncology treatment from RECIST terminology.

resource.name: ROI segmentation
resource.description: Description of the segmentation method used allowing the deffinition of a region of interest (ROI).

resource.name: Sequencing Analysis
resource.description: Sequencing analysis about a biological sample coming from a TumorPathologyEvent. This profile shows general information about the analysis done, additional omics results can be found in SNP, Fusion, CopyNumber, Expression and Annotation profiles.

resource.name: Sequencing Device
resource.description: Description of a sequencing device used for a Sequencing Analysis.

resource.name: Single Nucleotide Polymorphism
resource.description: Observation of a Single Nucleotide Polymorphism (SNP) derived from a Sequencing Analysis.

resource.name: Strand bias
resource.description: Indication of the existence of strand bias at the variant position

resource.name: TNM
resource.description: TNM Classification of malignant tumors used to indicate the tumor, node and metastasis state of a Tumor Pathology Event.

resource.name: Treatment
resource.description: Description of a treatment plan related to an Oncology Patient.

resource.name: Tumor Pathology Event
resource.description: Tumor Pathology Event (TPE) Condition describing a tumoral event: reference to the parent TPE, laterality, morphology.

resource.name: Tumor Pathology Event Parent
resource.description: Reference the Tumor Pathology Event from which the metastasis comes from.

resource.name: Tumor Pathology Event Type Value Set
Validation
resource.description: Validation information about data from a Variant / Expression / Fusion / CopyNumber profile.

resource.name: Variant Annotation
resource.description: The Annotation profile allows to add information about a SNP, a fusion, an expression or a copy number event. It is generally used to compare variant from a reference genome. There can be multiple instance of Variant Annotation Resource for one instance of SNP, CopyNumber, Expression or Fusion Resource.

resource.name: Variant Copy Number
resource.description: Observation of a Copy Number variant derived from a SequencingAnalysis. The CopyNumber profile is used to indicate the pathogenicity, the actionability, the loss of heterozygosity, the cytogenetic location, the start - end positions, the reference sequence assembly, the variation code, the segment intensity, the number of copy found and the Copy Number segment size.

resource.name: Vital Status
resource.description: Observation that indicates the last known Vital status of an Onco Patient.

resource.name: Weight and Height at the time of the Serie
resource.description: Weight and Height at the time of the Serie
